	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />The PPU is faster than the CPU so no, don't use 150ns chips as CHR RAM. You will be surely frustrated ... lol
<br />
<br />I'd suggest you go around "computer graveyards" and look for old 386s and 486s as their cache memory is VERY FAST SRAM memory (15ns/20ns, not 150ns) is usually socketed and can be bought for pennies most times. I have a box with like 60 62256 chips ranging from 30ns to 15ns.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


